Tuareg 1.37.2 is now available and moved to a new location.
                                                                  
It's goal is to provide a good support for Caml editing and debugging.
See the README file and on-line help for details.                 
                                                                  
Tuareg home page is now
http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~acohen/tuareg
For direct access to the archive, use
http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~acohen/tuareg/mode

Last changes include improvements in string/comment recognition
(hopefully the last!) and Emacs/XEmacs compatibility.

Tuareg is a constantly evolving GPL software: I'll be glad to receive
bug reports and comments!

